A financial consultant has declared her interest in the Nyeri Woman Rep seat. Rose Waikundi, launched her bid in Nyeri on Tuesday saying she will be vying for the seat under the Chama Cha Kazi party. Waikundi will now face-off with the incumbent Rahab Mukami and Margaret Karangaru, wife to former Nyeri governor the Nderitu Gachagua. Karungaru and Mukami are eyeing the UDA ticket. This is the second time Waikundi is vying for the seat. Waikundi who has been an advocate for women empowerment for 15 years, especially in table banking, said one of the key areas of focus will be on empowerment. “I know what our people need. They need training, social integration, exposure and network in SMEs, trade and career advancement,” she said. Also key in her manifesto is adding value to education which she said has been deteriorating in Nyeri. The aspirant said she will also ensure social balance and integration of the county in the national assembly is achieved. “I will also be focusing on mentorship.  We have many young people in this county who need somebody to hold their hands and a Woman Rep is supposed to bring gender balance and build all,” she said. Admitting that the boy child has been neglected in the society, she said that will be top of her priorities. “They will be my priority in my 100 days in office, I will unveiled a programme to improve the life of the boy child,” she said. Waikundi expressed her wish to work with like-minded leaders in Nyeri saying her campaigns will not focus on fighting other leaders but to build and mentor. “So I request all leaders to walk with me,” she said. She said she is ready to integrate everybody including professionals, business people and SMEs to ensure Nyeri prospers. (Edited by Tabnacha O)